channel.title: CVE Feed for Jenkins Project -- Jenkins RabbitMQ Consumer Plugin
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Jenkins Project -- Jenkins RabbitMQ Consumer Plugin

item.title: CVE-2023-24447|2023-10-24T12:48:38.939Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20rabbitmq%20consumer%20plugin
item.description: A cross-site request forgery (CSRF) vulnerability in Jenkins RabbitMQ Consumer Plugin 2.8 and earlier allows attackers to connect to an attacker-specified AMQP(S) URL using attacker-specified username and password.

item.title: CVE-2023-24448|2023-10-24T12:48:40.115Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20rabbitmq%20consumer%20plugin
item.description: A missing permission check in Jenkins RabbitMQ Consumer Plugin 2.8 and earlier allows attackers with Overall/Read permission to connect to an attacker-specified AMQP(S) URL using attacker-specified username and password.
